article.headline: Troy 64, Denver 46
article.story: TROY, Ala. -- Brandon Hazzard scored 23 points as Troy remained unbeaten in Sun Belt Conference play with a 64-46 victory over Denver on Saturday night. Richard Delk added 16 points for the Trojans (8-6, 3-0), including eight during an 18-4 run at the start of the second half that turned a 24-23 Pioneers halftime lead into a 41-28 Troy lead with 12:12 to play. Denver (10-5, 3-1) turned the ball over six times in that stretch, leading to eight of Troy's points. For the game, Troy scored 13 points off 11 Denver turnovers, while the Pioneers scored just two points off eight turnovers by the Trojans. Delk had five steals for Troy, which shot 56.5 percent (13-for-23) in the second half. Denver shot a season-low 39.1 percent (18-for-46) for the game. Andrew Hooper and Nate Rohnert scored nine points each and Rob Lewis eight to lead Denver.
